      "amount": "1 tablespoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "Light rum",
      "amount": "30ml"
    },
    {
      "name": "Water",
      "amount": "2 tablespoons"
    },
    {
      "name": "Cornstarch",
      "amount": "1 teaspoon",
      "notes": "Optional, for extra crispiness"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "In a small bowl whisk together gochujang, soy sauce, rice vinegar, honey, rum, and water to make the sauce.",
    "Heat 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large skillet over medium\u2011high heat. Add the chicken pieces and stir\u2011fry until golden brown and cooked through, about 5\u20136 minutes.",
    "Add minced garlic and stir for 30 seconds until fragrant.",
    "Pour the prepared sauce over the chicken and stir to coat. Cook for another 2 minutes to let the flavors meld.",
    "If you\u2019d like extra crispiness, sprinkle 1 teaspoon cornstarch over the chicken and stir until the sauce thickens, about 1 minute.",
    "Remove from heat and serve immediately over steamed rice or saut\u00e9ed vegetables. Enjoy!"
  ],
